column5: I've been exploring lots of new water this year with great success, but I haven't been taking too many pictures. Here's a few from the past week. Images are heavily cropped (apologies) because the fish came from water that was graciously shown to me. Thanks Solo.        I'll toss a few more up when I get them uploaded online.  Cheers.
What the heck, how about a couple more. This was a great morning - 2 hour drive to fish for 2 hours and get back to class for noon. Two hours filled with double headers and spunky northern bows.

Nice fish. I like the pink colour on the second pic in. I don't know if its just my crappy camera or something else that I'm missing because I never seem to be able to capture that rosy colour on the fish.
Nice fish Kemper. Got a pretty good idea where they were caught.
That fish was just really pink...had been in the system for a while
Those cropped images look awesome. They have that HD widescreen feel. Awesome
Hey is your neighbour Tim from Tool Time?  Can't see your face in any of those pictures
Previous experience has taught me that keeping my mug off the internet is in my best interest...
I hope you roped some of those fat hen browns, lol.
That's a page from a book I'm used to reading! Get up and fish for a few hours, then leave reluctantly to fulfill another obligation - in my case, work.  But, it beats not fishing at all  p.-
